WEBVTT

00:02.574 --> 00:04.875
I just read about
an experiment designed

00:04.877 --> 00:06.209
to see if you could
make two people fall

00:06.211 --> 00:08.145
in love in a matter of hours.

00:08.147 --> 00:09.713
That doesn't sound right.

00:09.715 --> 00:11.982
My research has shown that
it takes three to five years

00:11.984 --> 00:14.584
of shameless begging.

00:14.586 --> 00:17.621
Honey, neither of us comes off
good in that story.

00:17.623 --> 00:18.956
Yeah, I-I...

00:18.958 --> 00:21.158
I saw that article
you're talking about.

00:21.160 --> 00:23.193
Uh, the participants
ask each other a series

00:23.195 --> 00:25.829
of questions designed
to promote intimacy.

00:25.831 --> 00:27.197
And then they finish it off
by staring

00:27.199 --> 00:28.999
into each other's eyes
for four minutes.

00:29.001 --> 00:30.434
Oh, that's nonsense.

00:30.436 --> 00:32.569
I proclaimed my
love for you.

00:32.570 --> 00:34.171
And the last time I
looked into your eyes

00:34.173 --> 00:37.174
was when you thought
you had conjunctivitis.

00:37.176 --> 00:39.443
Other than the fact
that I had it,

00:39.445 --> 00:41.244
that was a magical night.

00:42.414 --> 00:45.148
Raj, would you ever try an
experiment like that with Emily?

00:45.150 --> 00:47.484
What? I don't need
science to win her heart.

00:47.486 --> 00:50.387
I have my family's
wealth for that.

00:50.389 --> 00:52.723
I'm telling you, you can't
create love in a few hours.

00:52.725 --> 00:54.424
Right?
Oh, careful.

00:54.426 --> 00:57.194
You're poking at the whole
foundation of <i> The Bachelor.</i>

00:57.196 --> 00:58.562
Yeah, but

00:58.564 --> 01:00.464
we don't have to debate this.

01:00.466 --> 01:01.732
We're scientists.

01:01.734 --> 01:03.867
We can conduct our own research.

01:03.869 --> 01:05.802
Yeah, I propose that we imprison

01:05.804 --> 01:07.104
two street people.
No.

01:07.106 --> 01:09.673
And...

01:09.675 --> 01:11.008
You didn't even let me finish.

01:11.010 --> 01:12.909
Forget it!
Oh!

01:12.911 --> 01:15.245
So, you can experiment
on all the apes you want.

01:15.247 --> 01:17.848
But I want to manipulate
the emotions of two captive

01:17.850 --> 01:20.817
human beings, suddenly
I'm the monster.

01:20.819 --> 01:22.486
Why don't you

01:22.488 --> 01:24.454
just do the test?

01:24.456 --> 01:27.591
In the interest of science,
I'd be willing to.

01:27.593 --> 01:29.192
What? You're okay with
an experiment where you have

01:29.194 --> 01:32.562
to answer awkward questions
about your innermost feelings?

01:32.564 --> 01:33.830
Yes.

01:33.832 --> 01:35.966
Please, can I do it
with him? Please?!

01:37.403 --> 01:39.636
I've been listening
to Sheldon's feelings on things

01:39.638 --> 01:42.172
for ten years.
Tag, you're it.

01:42.174 --> 01:44.841
Yeah, but what
if the experiment works?

01:44.843 --> 01:46.610
I'm not gonna fall
in love with Sheldon.

01:46.612 --> 01:47.677
That's what I said.

01:47.679 --> 01:49.246
Before I knew it,
he pontificated his way

01:49.248 --> 01:51.281
right into my heart.

01:51.283 --> 01:54.017
Uh, fun fact--
"pontificate"

01:54.019 --> 01:56.119
comes from the Latin
word "pontifex,"

01:56.121 --> 01:58.388
which means "bridge
builder" or "Pope."

02:00.059 --> 02:02.993
In love yet?

02:04.096 --> 02:07.731
